The paper deals with motion planning for a robot based on vision, which is a common topic in robotics (cs.RO). The use of a point-cloud camera and the optimization of manipulability suggest computer vision (cs.CV) as another likely category. The paper also involves optimization and multi-objective planning, which are common topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper deals with control of the robot during task execution, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
